All Superinterfaces:
IItem, IItemHandle, IUnmanagedItemHandle
All Known Subinterfaces:
IFolder, IVersionable
public interface IUnmanagedItem
extends IItem, IUnmanagedItemHandle

Represents an unmanaged item. Unmanaged items do not have a global notion of the current state, do not have basic CRUD service available at the repo API layer, and do not have query models. Generally these are not used directly by clients, but rather it is intended to be subclasses for source control and configuration management components.

Versionable items (such as file and folders) are created and manipulated in workspaces. Files and folders are the standard versionable item types.

Item handles and items are passive data objects that are retrieved or created while the client is logged in to a repository. These objects remain valid if the client logs out.

Since:
0.5
